&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Company&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div&gt;Avela is a Nobel Prize-winning, venture backed, seed-stage edtech/govtech startup focused on increasing access to high quality education with the first common application system for PK-12. We work with cities, school districts, and nonprofits to set up one-stop-shop enrollment hubs for families to find, navigate, and register for childcare, schools, summer camps, athletics, and other education, government, and social programs. We’re like “OpenTable for Education” or “Mindbody for Schools.”&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div&gt;We&#39;ve raised $6.4m from investors including Learn, Schmidt Futures, Ulu, Cherubic, and Urban Innovation Fund.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div&gt;Read more at avela.org/about.&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Team&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
